From df37631fec067596f2e7033c83703fb67962c79b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 01:22:26 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 03/27] [displayxr inline-3d #625 B2b] GPU<->browser weave Mojo
 bridge
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The canvas SharedImage + present live in the GPU process, but the weave RPC
client lives in the browser process (B2a; the GPU sandbox blocks the per-frame
RPC). B2b builds the bridge between them via the standard
ChildThread::BindHostReceiver -> GpuProcessHost::BindHostReceiver ->
ContentBrowserClient::BindGpuHostReceiver path (mirrors Chromecast's
VideoGeometrySetter). No new IPC plumbing — two embedder overrides + a mojom.

- content/shell/common/displayxr_weave.mojom: DisplayXRWeaver.WeaveSubmit(Rect)
  => (bool). B2c extends it with the pre-weave DXGIHandle in + woven handle +
  fence + eyes out.
- Browser: DisplayXRWeaverImpl (B2b: log + ok) + ShellContentBrowserClient::
  BindGpuHostReceiver (flag-gated, binds on the UI thread).
- GPU: ShellContentGpuClient::PostCompositorThreadCreated fires a one-shot
  WeaveSubmit probe via ChildThread::BindHostReceiver.

Validated on Leia: GPU process (pid A) WeaveSubmit -> browser process (pid B)
DisplayXRWeaverImpl -> reply ok=1. Distinct PIDs confirm the cross-process round
trip end to end.
